\subsection{RNN}
Well, RNN architecture is a vanilla RNN with a final predicting layer.

Here the input layer will be provided with the ten numbers whose rank to be predicted. And after that it predict 10 values for each input feature and then those 100 values are passed in output layer, which is then softmaxed to get the probabilities of each rank for the given number.

The output Layer helps RNN here to see the entire seq.

\textbf{Note: normal RNN will be very bad at predicting here , so this modification is added. }

