\subsubsection{Positional Encoding}
Well, as the embedding dimension is one, the positional encoding suggested by the paper will not work here. So, I used another system of encoding:

$$P_{pos} = (1.5)^{-pos}$$

\textbf{Note: any constant getter than 1 works.}

It has great properties: it is unique for every position; stays in (0,1]; and $1.5^(-9)$ is 0.026 which not negligible; can easily understood by the transformer. 

